&lt;p>Further event details, including &lt;a href="https://wowchemy.com/docs/writing-markdown-latex/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">page elements&lt;/a> such as image galleries, can be added to the body of this page.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Defense and Publication of MSc Thesis</title><link>https://pkaliosis.github.io/news/msc_thesis_published.html</link><pubDate>Fri, 01 Dec 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://pkaliosis.github.io/news/msc_thesis_published.html</guid><description>&lt;p>Last week, I had the opportunity to deliver a presentation on the research conducted during the course of my MSc thesis, titled &lt;a href="http://nlp.cs.aueb.gr/theses/p_kaliosis_msc_thesis.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">&amp;ldquo;Exploring Unimodal, Multimodal, and Few-shot Deep Learning Methods for Diagnostic Captioning.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a> The audience comprised members of the thesis committee, fellow students, distinguished researchers, and faculty members. This thesis was conducted under the supervision of Prof. &lt;a href="https://www2.aueb.gr/users/ion/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ion Androutsopoulos&lt;/a> and Prof. &lt;a href="https://ipavlopoulos.github.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">John Pavlopoulos&lt;/a>. The thesis committee consisted of the first supervisor, as well as Prof. &lt;a href="http://graphics.cs.aueb.gr/users/gepap/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">George Papaioannou&lt;/a> and Prof. &lt;a href="https://pages.aueb.gr/users/kotidis/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Yannis Kotidis&lt;/a>.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Wave in graphene</title><link>https://pkaliosis.github.io/gallery/graphene.html</link><pubDate>Sun, 15 Oct 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://pkaliosis.github.io/gallery/graphene.html</guid><description/></item><item><title>Fullerene collision</title><link>https://pkaliosis.github.io/gallery/fullrene.html</link><pubDate>Tue, 10 Oct 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://pkaliosis.github.io/gallery/fullrene.html</guid><description/></item><item><title>Distinction in the annual ImageCLEFmedical Competition</title><link>https://pkaliosis.github.io/news/clef-distinction/clef-distinction.html</link><pubDate>Thu, 05 Oct 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://pkaliosis.github.io/news/clef-distinction/clef-distinction.html</guid><description>&lt;p>We participated in the annual &lt;a href="https://www.imageclef.org/2023/medical/caption" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ImageCLEFmedical Caption&lt;/a> competition, where we ranked 1st in the Concept Detection and 3rd in the Caption Prediction task. This is a distinction that our group has been systematically achieving for the last few years. You can read more &lt;a href="https://www.athenarc.gr/en/news/distinction-international-artificial-intelligence-competition" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here&lt;/a>.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>The molecular ring</title><link>https://pkaliosis.github.io/gallery/ring.html</link><pubDate>Thu, 05 Oct 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://pkaliosis.github.io/gallery/ring.html</guid><description/></item><item><title>Assessing the validity of NMR relaxation rates obtained from coarse-grained simulations of PEG-water mixtures</title><link>https://pkaliosis.github.io/publication/2023-reconsruction-of-nmr.html</link><pubDate>Fri, 16 Jun 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://pkaliosis.github.io/publication/2023-reconsruction-of-nmr.html</guid><description/></item><item><title>Stability of Binary Precipitates in Cu-Ni-Si-Cr Alloys Investigated Through Active Learning</title><link>https://pkaliosis.github.io/publication/2023-stability-of-binary.html</link><pubDate>Wed, 14 Jun 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://pkaliosis.github.io/publication/2023-stability-of-binary.html</guid><description/></item><item><title>NMR Investigation of Water in Salt Crusts: Insights from Experiments and Molecular Simulations</title><link>https://pkaliosis.github.io/publicatio